{#def hex, name="", selected=false, size="md", disabled=false #}
{#
  A single workspace-color swatch: a circular radio button rendering one
  palette (or custom) color. Used by the workspace-settings picker and the
  create-form picker, which both render a row of these plus their own
  per-page JS for click handling / saving.

  This component owns only the markup contract the picker JS depends on:
    - class ``color-swatch`` (the rim + selection-ring styles live in
      app.css; ``#create-color-picker .color-swatch`` overrides the rim
      to 1px for the smaller create-form size)
    - ``role="radio"`` + ``aria-checked`` for the selection state
    - ``data-color`` (the #rrggbb the JS reads on click)
    - ``aria-label`` (the palette name, for screen readers)
  Keeping this in one place means the JS selectors and the rendered
  attributes can't drift apart across the two call sites.

  Props:
    hex       -- the swatch color as #rrggbb; sets both the visible
                 background and the data-color the JS reads.
    name      -- palette name, surfaced only as the aria-label.
    selected  -- when true, aria-checked="true" (drives the accent ring).
    size      -- "md" (34px, settings picker) or "sm" (24px, create form).
    disabled  -- when true, renders the button disabled (stale workspace).
#}
{%- set _sizes = {"md": "w-[34px] h-[34px]", "sm": "w-6 h-6"} -%}
{%- set _cls = "color-swatch " ~ _sizes[size] ~ " rounded-full focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent/60 disabled:opacity-40" -%}
<button type="button"
        role="radio"
        class="{{ _cls }}"
        aria-label="{{ name }}"
        aria-checked="{{ 'true' if selected else 'false' }}"
        data-color="{{ hex }}"
        style="background-color: {{ hex }};"
        {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}></button>
